# packages.list — Proxmox-ISO-t2
# Documents T2-specific package additions to the official Proxmox VE ISO.
# All base Proxmox VE packages are inherited from the upstream ISO unchanged.
# This file is for reference only; the build scripts use it as documentation.

# ── T2 KERNEL ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Source: https://github.com/AdityaGarg8/pve-edge-kernel-t2/releases
# Format: pve-kernel-* — integrates with proxmox-boot-tool natively
pve-kernel-VERSION-t2        # T2-patched Proxmox VE kernel (apple-bce built in)
pve-headers-VERSION-t2       # Kernel headers (for any DKMS modules)

# ── T2 HARDWARE SUPPORT ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Source: https://github.com/AdityaGarg8/t2-ubuntu-repo (bookworm APT repo)
apple-t2-audio-config        # ALSA/PipeWire DSP config for T2 HDA audio device
tiny-dfr                     # Touch Bar userspace daemon (optional, skip on Mac mini)

# ── BROADCOM WIFI DRIVER ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Same approach as EndeavourOS-ISO-t2 (which uses broadcom-wl on Arch).
# Out-of-tree wl driver — no Apple firmware blobs needed, works offline.
# The wl.ko module is built at ISO build time via DKMS.
# Source: Debian non-free repository
dkms                         # DKMS framework
broadcom-sta-dkms            # Broadcom out-of-tree wl driver (Debian equiv of broadcom-wl)
broadcom-sta-common          # Supporting files for broadcom-sta

# ── STANDARD PROXMOX VE PACKAGES (inherited from official ISO) ────────────────
# proxmox-ve              — meta-package (pulls all components)
# pve-manager             — web management interface
# pve-kernel-*            — standard Proxmox kernel (replaced by T2 kernel above)
# qemu-server             — VM/KVM support
# pve-lxc / lxc          — Linux Container support
# pve-firewall            — firewall management
# corosync                — cluster communication
# postfix                 — mail transport
# open-iscsi              — iSCSI initiator
# zfsutils-linux          — ZFS userspace tools
# (and many more — see official Proxmox VE package list)
